      {
        "id": 5,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 6,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Falling Action",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "End of Act 2:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The Falling Action explores the aftermath of the Climax and contains a series of events that untangle the main conflict and lead to the Resolution. Events continue to trend in a new direction for the Protagonist as loose ends begin to be tied up. Unexpected incidents add suspense to the final outcome, and the story starts winding down to its conclusion."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Introduce further complications that mirror the new normal of the world after the Climax."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "How do the Characters respond to the results of the Climax?"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Increase tension and stakes as the story rushes towards the Resolution and final suspense."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Continue to make things worse for the Protagonist, but leave room for a bit of hope."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example – Hamlet:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Hamlet is sent away. Laertes returns from France to avenge his father's death, and Claudius and Laertes conspire to kill Hamlet. Hamlet returns to Elsinore. Ophelia goes mad and dies when she falls from a willow tree into a brook and drowns."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 2 makes up 50% of the story from 25% - 75%."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The Falling Action occurs around the 65% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
