      {
        "id": 4,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 5,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Climax",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Middle of Act 2:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The crux of the story and the height of suspense and tension. This is the turning point for the story and Protagonist, and it is important to put full effort into writing this scene. In a tragedy, here is where everything turns and begins to fall apart. In a comedy, things have been difficult for the Protagonist, but they start to improve at this point."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The Protagonist is at full capacity and ready to act – consider how their actions at this juncture will transform the story and their character arc."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Address the Central Conflict and demonstrate the fate of the Protagonist."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Turn the tides on the Protagonist: if they have been succeeding, here they fail; if they have been failing, here they succeed."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example – Hamlet:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The play has successfully proven to Hamlet that the King is guilty of the murder... and Hamlet actually goes mad. Hamlet wants to kill the King but does not want to do so while the King is in confession and praying. Hamlet accidentally kills Polonius when he mistakes him for King Claudius."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 2 makes up 50% of the story from 25% - 75%."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The Climax occurs around the 50% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
