      {
        "id": 3,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 4,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Rising Action",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Beginning of Act 2:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Major events lead toward the Climax while increasing the tension and stakes. This section explores the story's conflict and complications while offering the reader key pieces of backstory. The Protagonist's motives are revealed as well as their inner conflict and the central theme of the story. The Protagonist sees things go from bad to worse."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Introduce any Central Characters not yet revealed."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Create several points of conflict and complications as things get worse for the Protagonist."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Create each conflict and complication to lead to the Climax and its aftermath."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example – Hamlet:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Hamlet pretends to be mad but begins to descend into actual madness. Growing suspicious, King Claudius begins spying on Hamlet, sees him as a threat, and decides he should be sent away; time is running out for Hamlet as the stakes rise. Hamlet presents the Mouse Trap play within a play to gauge the reaction of King Claudius and assess his guilt."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 2 makes up 50% of the story from 25% - 75%."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The Rising Action occurs around the 25% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
