      {
        "id": 2,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 3,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Inciting Incident",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above this Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "End of Act 1:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The first point of conflict and the moment that propels the Protagonist into the story. This event begins the Central Conflict of the story and must be one that cannot be resolved on its own."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Tie the Inciting Incident to the basic conflict within the story, hinted at in the Exposition."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Create a strong Inciting Incident that ultimately forces the Protagonist's hand toward taking action."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Ensure the Incident and the Protagonist's reaction to it are intriguing enough to keep the reader's attention and hook them deeper into the story."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Example – Hamlet:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Hamlet meets the Ghost and learns that King Hamlet was, in fact, murdered by his brother Claudius, now on the throne and married to Hamlet's mother. The Ghost of Hamlet's father demands Hamlet seek revenge for his murder. Hamlet is unsure whether the Ghost is trustworthy or a Devil trying to trick him."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 1 makes up the first 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The Inciting Incident occurs around the 15% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
